    "7217718": {
        "Desc": "Gather the three fragments",
        "Tips": "Go to Quest Menu to access Quest Hints",
        "Talk": [
            [
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "Is there anything I can help you with?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "About the fragment at the Evernight Temple..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "The fragment is said to have been hidden in a secret part of the Temple. Its gates will only open at night."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "The fragment contains the power of the \"Serpent-Seeker Rule,\" which will attract Vishaps."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "As such, you can follow their trail to find the fragment. But there will be monsters remaining there and standing guard, so it is best to be careful."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "Tell me about the fragment at the Serpent's Heart..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "The Serpent's Heart is home to an altar that is considered the heart of the Cosmic Serpent. Before the coming of Watatsumi Omikami, we called this place The Heart of Ouroboros."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "It is, in essence, a sealing device for storing important objects. Using a phenomenon unique to Enkanomiya known as the Sunfire Phantasms, we added another dimension of possibilities to that device."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "As such, that place was already known as Delphi, the Serpent's Land, even before the coming of Watatsumi Omikami."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "The proper entry procedures must be followed in strict order to retrieve the corresponding objects from their locations. As such, this place can also be used to imprison criminals."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "The codes have been scattered throughout Enkanomiya. If you find them, some other rewards may yet await."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "One of the fragments is within the altar. As for any secret messages regarding it, they should be found near the altar — it took a real scolding from Lady Eboshi before those were added in, too."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "By the way, when you are out searching for clues, watch out for Enkanomiya's Whitenight and Evernight states."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "There is also a type of ley line phenomenon here known as Sunfire Phantasms. As the land phases between Whitenight and Evernight, energy will gather and disperse. This can cause objects to be hidden or become visible."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "If you cannot find clues but discover certain irregularities, try switching between day and night."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "As for the fragment at the Narrows..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "The ruins of the Narrows contains a hidden chamber. Its exact position is yours to discover alone."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "The entrance to the chamber has been concealed by a Sunfire Phantasm. It can only be revealed by switching between Whitenight and Evernight."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "In later days, we would come to grasp the phenomenon known as the Sunfire Phantasms and use them to conceal secrets."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "Matters related to the trial are of utmost secrecy, so please, simply rely on your observational skills and the changes between night and day to explore on your own."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "I've got nothing else to ask..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "Understood. If you require help, feel free to seek me out at any time — though I fear that I can only answer specific questions you may have in my current state..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aru",
                    "T": "Good luck."
                }
            ]
        ]
    },
    "7217719": {
        "Desc": "Gather the three fragments",
        "Tips": "Go to Quest Menu to access Quest Hints",
        "Talk": [
            [
                {
                    "N": "Enjou",
                    "T": "These afterimages really are interesting..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "About the movement of the sun and moon here..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Enjou",
                    "T": "Well, we are underground, so there is no sun here. That is why the people here created this lighthouse."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Enjou",
                    "T": "Through this and perhaps other devices as well, the rulers of Byakuyakoku could adjust a solar and lunar cycle, thus alternating between Whitenight and Evernight."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Enjou",
                    "T": "In ancient times, the Dainichi Mikoshi's name was \"Hyperion,\" which refers to the main body of the sun in the ancient tongue."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Enjou",
                    "T": "I can understand their sentiments. Everything must have been hard, living in a realm bereft of the sun."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "Is there anything else you know about Byakuyakoku?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Enjou",
                    "T": "Byakuyakoku has a tradition of triangle worship."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Enjou",
                    "T": "They believed that Byakuyakoku was the intersection between three realms: the Vishap Realm, the Human Realm, and the Void Realm."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Enjou",
                    "T": "The three trial sites on the border were originally watch-posts against the Vishaps, and they were also a spiritual junction for the three powers that flowed through Enkanomiya."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Enjou",
                    "T": "In that triangular formation of nature, there was an opposition between the abyssal Void Realm and the elemental Vishap Realm."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Enjou",
                    "T": "Humans would create high towers in later years to allow the Human Realm to interpose itself between the two, thus creating a stable space — one held up by three towers in three corners."
                }
            ]
        ]
    },
